{
  "texts": [
    "In this way, the prior models were re-evaluated, and the SOTA model turned out to be 'BatteryBERT (cased)', identical to that reported (Fig. 5a).",
    "We tested the zero-shot QA model using the GPT-3.5 model ('textdavinci-003'), yielding a precision of 60.92%, recall of 79.96%, and F1 score of 69.15% (Fig. 5b and Supplementary Table 3).",
    "These relatively low performance values can be derived from the domain-specific dataset, from which it is difficult for a vanilla model to find the answer from the given scientific literature text.",
    "Therefore, we added a task-informing phrase such as 'The task is to extract answers from the given text.'",
    "to the existing prompt consisting of the question, context, and answer."
  ]
}